	(text_box "Do not forget to bridge this jumper after testing the boost converter.\n\nDo not plug in the ASW module until this jumper has been bridged."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 90.17 43.18 0)
		(size 40.64 12.7)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type default)
			(color 255 0 0 1)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Liberation Mono")
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.508)
				(bold yes)
				(color 255 0 0 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "5123e165-661c-47b6-8c92-4cb884f6eef5")
	)
	(text_box "The diodes and resistors within the blue dash-dot boxes serve primarily as a safety mechanism during development. They are intended to absorb high voltage in the event of short circuits caused by firmware bugs. To ensure that the total current absorbed from Vpp3_HV_UPDI remains below 30 mA under worst-case conditions (e.g., multiple short circuits), maintain Vdd0 at or above 4.5 V and avoid selecting a high voltage exceeding 11 V. Otherwise, standard operating voltages may be used.\n\nAlthough these components may remain connected beyond development mode, disconnecting them can reduce voltage drop and enhance performance by minimizing stray capacitance. To disable them, cut the diode jumpers and bridge the resistor jumpers."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 88.9 90.17 0)
		(size 68.58 22.86)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type default)
			(color 0 0 255 1)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
